San Francisco's Cable Cars
Woodford Press | 1995 | 0942627121 | English | 148 pages | PDF | 23.6 MB

An in-depth look at the history of cable cars and how they helped shape San Francisco. Jansen has competently sifted the original documents and secondary sources. She relates the economic & political factors that built the lines and their influence upon the growing city. Heavily and well-illustrated. Scholar and fan alike will cherish the book
